---
description: Rundler test and ERC-4337 compliance guidance
globs:
  - "**/*test*.rs"
  - "test/spec-tests/**"
  - ".github/workflows/ci.yaml"
  - ".github/workflows/unit.yaml"
  - ".github/workflows/compliance.yaml"
---

- Prefer co-located `#[cfg(test)]` module tests for Rust behavior changes.
- Reuse existing mockall and manual mock patterns instead of mocking unrelated layers.
- Run `make test-unit` before handoff for code changes.
- Run integrated or modular spec tests for RPC, EntryPoint, pool, simulation, or builder-flow changes.
- CI compliance currently covers v0.6, v0.7, and v0.8 through the bundler test executor.

Full details: `.agents/skills/testing-compliance/`.
